OL,3,CMetro disruption as fleet undergoes
OL,4,Cfault checks which 'will take several
OL,5,Cdays'
OL,7,F"They need time to check the whole
OL,8,Ffleet and replace any faulty parts, to
OL,9,Favoid the risk of the overhead wire
OL,10,Fbeing pulled down causing more serious
OL,11,Fdisruption.
OL,13,F"These checks will take several days
OL,14,Fbut we will keep customers updated
OL,15,Fabout the impact on Metro services."
OL,17,FThe pantograph - the stick of metal
OL,18,Fbetween the train and the overhead
OL,19,Flines - has a part on it called a
OL,20,Fcarbon strip.
